Oh, and on that note, products tend to have much bigger

00:07:52.869 --> 00:07:56.770
barcodes, so they are easier and quicker to scan.

00:07:57.480 --> 00:08:02.740
If you have never been to an ALDI or Lidl, or you live in a country where these supermarkets

00:08:02.750 --> 00:08:08.010
don’t have a presence, you might well be thinking “Alastair, they don’t sound very good!”.

00:08:08.900 --> 00:08:14.160
But what would probably be a very pleasant surprise would be after the person

00:08:14.160 --> 00:08:18.820
at the checkout has scanned all of your shopping basket and told you the price.

